## ADDENDUM — discriminated union for tool outcome (later session)
===================================================================
Following the user's "use discriminated unions where they make sense", modeled
endToolSpan's terminal outcome as a tagged union instead of {result?, error?}:
  type ToolSpanOutcome =
    | {kind:'result'; result: Record<string,unknown> | null}
    | {kind:'error'; error: Error}
Call sites pass {kind:'result',...} / {kind:'error',...}; the body branches on
`outcome.kind`. This makes the result-XOR-error contract explicit and rejects
the previously-representable invalid states (both set / neither set). The
result `| null` is retained (tool return values can legitimately be null).
Verified tsc esm+cjs, eslint, prettier, slice-03 jest 22/22.

